body_html:
I see the same error on both Mac OS 10.11.16 and Raspbian. Clean git checkout of Tensorflow in both cases.

$ uname -a
Darwin XXXX.local 15.6.0 Darwin Kernel Version 15.6.0: Mon Aug 29 20:21:34 PDT 2016; root:xnu-3248.60.11~1/RELEASE_X86_64 x86_64

$ tensorflow/contrib/makefile/download_dependencies.sh
downloading http://bitbucket.org/eigen/eigen/get/" + eigen_version + ".tar.gz
tar: Unrecognized archive format
tar: Error exit delayed from previous errors.
Ripley:tensorflow andrew

$ uname -a
Linux raspberrypi 4.1.19+ #858 Tue Mar 15 15:52:03 GMT 2016 armv6l GNU/Linux

$ tensorflow/contrib/makefile/download_dependencies.sh
downloading http://bitbucket.org/eigen/eigen/get/" + eigen_version + ".tar.gz

gzip: stdin: not in gzip format
tar: Child returned status 1
tar: Error is not recoverable: exiting now

Edited:
For those who just want to get it to work, change the EIGEN_URL line in download_dependencies.sh to:

EIGEN_URL="http://bitbucket.org/eigen/eigen/get/46ee714e25d5.tar.gz"
